This paper discusses the optimization of web page links to improve user satisfaction and retrieval system efficiency. This topic falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also discusses user experience and interface design, which are relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The proposed model for displaying popular links involves machine learning techniques, which falls under the Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-category. The paper also discusses indexing and retrieval systems, which are relevant to the Search Engines and Information Retrieval (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method to increase the quality of retrieval systems, which is relevant to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
